correctness.rationale: The extraction contains numerous fabricated or non-traceable values and at least one schema violation. Specific issues: (1) Schema violation: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null but the schema expects an object; if not PEALD, this field should be omitted. (2) Substrate: reported as “5×5 cm² gold substrate,” whereas the article uses a gold-coated quartz crystal electrode (QCM) as the substrate; 5×5 cm² describes reactor capacity, not the actual sample. (3) Pressure: a numeric value of 1.0 mmHg is given, but the article only mentions “a few mbar” without a specific number; the provided value is not traceable. (4) Thickness/cycles: numberofCycles = 600 and filmThickness = 1050 nm are not reported anywhere in the article; they are invented. (5) Flow rates: precursor/co-reactant/purge flows (10/10/100 sccm) are not provided by the article; invented. (6) Material properties: refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, mobility, uniformity, conformality, elemental concentration and atomic ratio, roughness, and film density (and its XRR method) are all absent from the article; these values are fabricated. In addition, the film density value and unit pairing are inconsistent with the article’s 5.675 g cm^-3 reference (the schema unit used corresponds to g/dm^3), and XRR was not reported. (7) Device properties: all TFT metrics and device structure are not discussed in the article; fabricated. (8) SupercycleDesign provided as empty arrays is unnecessary (binary ALD) but not a hard violation; however many other fields above are incorrect. Correct elements include: reactor (F120, Microchemistry), temperature (140 °C), precursors (DEZn/H2O), carrier/purging gas (N2), pulse and purge times (200/500 ms), saturation behavior, and an induction/nucleation period on the order of 30–40 cycles. To correct: remove or leave unspecified any values not reported (pressure numeric, flow rates, film/device properties, filmThickness, numberofCycles), fix substrate description, and remove the null plasmaPower field; retain only values explicitly supported by the text (e.g., 140 °C, pulse/purge times, DEZn/H2O, N2, qualitative saturation and nucleation period).

completeness.rationale: Significant incompleteness and schema deviations. (1) Multiple processes in the article are not represented: distinct runs include growth on bare gold at 140 °C (Fig. 2), on ZnO-precovered substrates with varying interruption times (Fig. 3), temperature sweeps 25–220 °C including the ALE window (130–180 °C; Figs. 7–8), pulse-length variations for DEZ and H2O (Figs. 5–6), and XRD films on glass (Fig. 9). Only one process instance is provided. (2) Many values are untraceable to the article: reactor pressure (set to 1 mmHg), all flow rates, number of cycles (600), final film thickness (1050 nm), optical properties (RI, bandgap, absorption), electrical properties (resistivity, mobility, carrier density), uniformity, conformality, film composition/XPS, roughness value, device metrics, safety, stability, reproducibility—none are reported by the paper. (3) Inconsistencies: filmThickness (1050 nm) conflicts with 600 cycles × 1.75 Å/cycle = 105 nm; filmDensity unit/value mismatch (5.675 g/dm³ given, but ZnO ≈ 5.675 g/cm³ ≈ 5675 g/dm³). (4) Schema issues: processParameters includes plasmaPower: null (type violation) and an extra filmThickness field at the processParameters level (not defined; additionalProperties=false), and duplicate thickness entries. (5) While some fields are correct/traceable (TALD, DEZ/H₂O, N₂ carrier/purge, F120 Microchemistry reactor, dosing/purge times, 140 °C example, saturation behavior, nucleation period ≈30–40 cycles), the extraction is largely unsupported by the text and misses multiple processes. Review/remove unsubstantiated fields, correct units and internal consistency, and add separate process entries for the different substrates/temperatures/pulse-length experiments.
